  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">William Lloyd Garrison discusses his reply to &quot;Mr. Phillips unjust allegations against Mr. Quincy, Mr. May and myself, concerning the Jackson legacy.&quot; Garrison elaborates on the matter: &quot;That reply, as you can easily imagine, caused me an aching heart in writing it, in view of the close and tender relations which have so long subsisted between Mr. P. and myself, and of the more than probability that it will prevent our meeting again as old friends and confidants.&quot;</subfield>
  </datafield>
  <datafield tag="500" ind1=" " ind2=" ">
    <subfield code="a">Includes, accompanying envelope with the delivery address: &quot;Miss Anne Warren Weston, Weymouth, Mass.&quot;</subfield>
